          stepNumber: 1,
          instruction: "FOR THE PRALINE: Line rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper; spray parchment with vegetable oil spray and set aside. Bring sugar, water, and lemon juice to boil in medium saucepan over medium heat, stirring once or twice to dissolve sugar. Cook, without stirring, until syrup is golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes. Remove saucepan from heat, stir in hazelnuts, and immediately pour mixture onto prepared sheet. Place sheet on wire rack and allow caramel to harden, about 30 minutes."
